title: This Week’s Gridiron Matchups
text:
High school football games involving schools from Barbour County: 
All Games kickoff at 7 p.m. 
FRIDAY, Oct. 2 
WHO: B.T. Washington Golden Eagles at Eufaula Tigers 
WHERE: at Tiger Stadium, Eufaula 
SERIES: Eufaula leads, 18-0 
LAST MEETING: 2014, Eufaula 34, B.T. Washington 16 
Records: Dale County (2-3, 1-2); Eufaula (4-1, 2-0) 
COACHES: Maurice Heard (10-34 in fifth season at B.T. Washington); Bryan Moore (4-1 in first season at Eufaula) 
Noteworthy: Eufaula has never lost to B.T. Washington, dating back to the first of 18 meetings in 1991. Eight of those wins have been via shutout. The most points the Golden Eagles ever scored on the Tigers were 19 in a 46-19 loss in 2012. Overall, Eufaula has outscored its Tuskegee opponent, 556-134. 
WHO: Evangel Christian Academy at Lakeside School Chiefs 
WHERE: at Reeves Field, Eufaula 
SERIES: Lakeside leads, 7-3 
LAST MEETING: 2014, Lakeside 35, Evangel Christian 6 
RECORDS: Evangel Christian (2-3, 1-1); Lakeside School (3-2, 2-1) 
COACHES: Andy Whatley (10-25 in fourth season at Evangel Christian); Keith Jones (3-2 in first season at Lakeside) 
Noteworthy: Lakeside is on a two-game losing streak. Last year, after losing to the same two teams (Glenwood and Edgewood Academy), the Chiefs reeled off four straight wins. They started that win streak with a lopsided win at Evangel Christian Academy. 
WHO: Pike County Bulldogs at Barbour County Jaguars 
WHERE: at Jaguar Stadium, Clayton 
SERIES: Pike County leads, 3-2 
LAST MEETING: 2014, Pike County 54,, Barbour County 0 
RECORDS: Pike County (4-0, 2-0); Barbour County (0-6, 0-3) 
COACHES: Fred Holland (21-16 in fourth season at Pike County); Chris Reynolds (0-16 in second season at Barbour County) 
Noteworthy: Pike County has shut out all four opponents this season by a combined score of 213-0. Barbour County has been outscored 228-47.
